<div xmlns:perseus="http://www.perseus.org/meta/perseus.rdfs#" xmlns:dctype="http://purl.org/dc/dcmitype/" xmlns:tufts="http://www.tufts.edu/" xmlns:alph="http://alpheios.net/namespaces/tei" class="alpheios-lex-text_container en">
    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n3332" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔοικα</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ϝέϝοικα</span>), 3 du. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔικτον</span>,
          part. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐοικώς, εἰκώς</span>, fem. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εἰκυῖα, ἐικυῖα, ἰκυῖα</span>, pl. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εἰοικυῖαι</span>, plup. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐῴκειν</span>, du. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐίκτην</span>, 3 pl.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐοίκεσαν</span>, also <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔικτο, ἤικτο</span> (an ipf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εἶκε</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 18.520</span></i>, is by
          some referred here, by others to <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εἴκω</span>): (1) <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">be like, resemble</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τινί</span> (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τι</span>),
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄντα, εἰς ὦπα,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Od. 1.208</span></i>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc"> Ω
            630</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 3.158</span></i>; ‘I seem to
          be singing in the presence of a god when I sing by thee’ (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔοικα</span> = videor mihi), <i><span class="en">Od. 22.348</span></i>. —(2) impers., <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">be
            fitting, suitable, be-</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">seem;</span> abs., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">οὐδὲ
            ϝέϝοικεν</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 1.119</span></i>, and
          w. dat. of person, <i><span class="en">Il. 9.70</span></i>, also w.
          acc. and inf., <i><span class="en">Il. 2.190</span></i>; freq. the
          part. as adj., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μῦθοι ἐοικότες,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Od. 3.124</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">
            ἐοικότα μῡθήσασθαι, καταλέξαι, γ 125</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 4.239</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
